The other approach is based on survey data on peopleâ€™s predictions of the SWB
consequences of different possible choices. Researchers ask whether peopleâ€™s (hypothetical or
actual) choices coincide with what they believe would maximize their SWB (Benjamin, Heffetz,
Kimball, and Rees-Jones, 2012, 2014; Fleurbaey and Schwandt, 2016; Adler, Dolan, and
Kavetsos, 2017; SzabÃ³ and Ujhelyi, 2017).5 For example, Benjamin, Heffetz, Kimball, and ReesJones (2014) ask graduating medical students to report their just-submitted ranking over
residency programs, and to predict their SWB under each program. While the students usually

